OL,6,FHe then forced the masked robber out
OL,7,Fof the door.
OL,9,FSpeaking after the incident, Mr Croker
OL,10,Ftold ITV News Calendar: "I do think
OL,11,Fabout it a lot. It's not as if you can
OL,12,Fswitch off and it's out of mind - I
OL,13,Fcan't do that.
OL,15,F"I find it worse when I go to bed at
OL,16,Fnight and close my eyes, I can see
OL,17,Fhim. It plays on my mind more, just
OL,18,Fthinking about it."
