OL,6,FRebecca Stevens, for Smith, said: "He
OL,7,Fis thoroughly ashamed of himself ...
OL,8,Fand bitterly regrets the decision he
OL,9,Fmade that day.
OL,11,F"Since then he has been incredibly
OL,12,Fremorseful and keen to offer an
OL,13,Fapology and wanted to know Mr Croker
OL,14,Fwas all right."
OL,16,FDet Insp Lucy Garside, of Rotherham
OL,17,FCID, said: "Smith's actions were
OL,18,Freprehensible, he tried to intimidate
OL,19,Fand rob a man twice his age, but has
OL,20,Finstead earned himself time behind
OL,21,Fbars.
